        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 6:46PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 645 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Dublin, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Radford...
Pulaski...
Dublin...
Poplar Hill...
Claytor Dam...
Fairlawn...
and Mc Coy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
